<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 4:26PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN CHARLOTTE AND EAST
CENTRAL HALIFAX COUNTIES THROUGH 500 PM EDT...
At 426 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Redoak, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Redoak...
Clover...
Drakes Branch...
Staunton River State Park...
Dryburg...
Wylliesburg...
and Saxe.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
